  "exploit_path": {
    "summary": "The incident began on October 1, 2024, when an attacker operating from address 0x9776c0abe8ae3c9ca958875128f1ae1d5afafcb8 executed a price manipulation attack on Ethereum mainnet. The primary attack transaction (0xd20b3b31a682322eb0698ecd67a6d8a040ccea653ba429ec73e3584fa176ff2b) involved multiple address interactions, including 0x81F48A87Ec44208c691f870b9d400D9c13111e2E, 0x9793d1082ecad9d813bbf7e044162fb0d8d29c9f, and 0x32fd502975d5b74686e34df01aa8b8b28e213aad. Based on the incident classification, the attacker likely manipulated oracle price feeds or exploited insufficient price validation mechanisms to extract value from the protocol. The attack succeeded in draining approximately 8 units of value, though the exact asset type and protocol specifics remain under investigation. Multiple intermediary addresses were used in the attack flow, suggesting a coordinated and premeditated exploitation strategy.",
